commit.title: Remove evar map from Proofview.Goal.t
commit.message:
Remove evar map from Proofview.Goal.t

When we modify the evar map, we would end up with an outdated one in
the Goal.t which may cause evar map leaks.

We change the enter API to pass the current evar map to the
function (ie [enter : (evar_map -> goal -> unit tactic) -> unit
tactic]) instead of letting the caller do tclEVARMAP as otherwise
porting while taking into account the exception catching behaviour of
enter would be hell ([enter (fun sigma g -> raise Foo)] and
[enter (fun g -> tclEVARMAP >>= fun sigma -> raise Foo)] are different).

When we modify the evar map, we would end up with an outdated one in
the Goal.t which may cause evar map leaks.

We change the enter API to pass the current evar map to the
function (ie [enter : (evar_map -> goal -> unit tactic) -> unit
tactic]) instead of letting the caller do tclEVARMAP as otherwise
porting while taking into account the exception catching behaviour of
enter would be hell ([enter (fun sigma g -> raise Foo)] and
[enter (fun g -> tclEVARMAP >>= fun sigma -> raise Foo)] are different).
